  "text": "Servo's style system uses the selectors and stylo crates from github.com/servo/stylo as workspace dependencies declared in the root Cargo.toml (selectors at rev 3b46f3ef, stylo at same rev). The layout component (components/layout/Cargo.toml) depends on both selectors and stylo, and components/layout/style_ext.rs extensively uses stylo types (ComputedValues, BorderStyle, WritingMode, etc.) for layout computation. The script component (components/script/Cargo.toml) also depends on selectors, stylo, stylo_atoms, stylo_dom, and stylo_traits. The Rust compiler does not share CSS selectors code with Servo -- the selectors crate is Servo/stylo-specific. However, Rust's proc_macro bridge (library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs) defines the with_api macro for client-server RPC, with client.rs and server.rs implementing the bridge. The compiler-side proc_macro integration is in compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro.rs, which implements MessagePipe for the bridge server. This proc_macro infrastructure enables Servo's extensive use of derive macros across its codebase.",
